Wash and dry all produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, core, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1} crosswise into strips.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If needed, add a splash of water to help poblano soften.

While poblano cooks, drain and rinse @black beans{13.4%ounce}.

Once poblano is softened, stir in scallion whites and @southwest spice blend{2%teaspoons}.

> Be sure to measure the Southwest Spice—we sent more.

Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add beans, @Tex-Mex paste{1}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring, until filling is combined and thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Sprinkle black bean filling with @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Cover pan until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with black bean filling, @smoky red pepper crema{2%tablespoons}, and scallion greens. Serve.